REALITY TV stars Brinnette Seopela, Christall Kay and DJ Tira’s wife Gugu Khathi are said to have been left out of the upcoming season of the Real Housewives of Johannesburg. Christall and Brinnette were part of the first and second seasons, while Gugu was going to be a new cast member for season 3. According to City Press, Christall was not contacted to feature on the next season. “Christall confirmed that she has been left in the dark for a long time as she was not aware that season 3 was coming until recently. She was not aware that they are preparing for the new season,” wrote City Press. ALSO READ : LADY DU AND ANDILE MXAKAZA SPLIT The publication said Brinnette and Gugu also confirmed they wouldn’t be part of the show. “Brinnette is adamant she won’t feature for season 3. She cited personal reasons. Gugu did not say much as she does not want to be associated with the reality TV show anymore,” read the article. Season 3 was set to return in 2021 but production was stopped when the trio allegedly fought. Last year, it was reported that Gugu and Brinnette fought with Christall and she opened an assault case against them. She was allegedly left with a bruised face. The cast members for season 3 will be announced next month.